.TH DHCP 8
.SH NAME
dhcp \- DHCP client configuration for ktcp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ktcp
.RB [ \-d ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B DHCP
is a client side implementation of the DHCP protocol.
It automatically negotiates an IP address, netmask, and default gateway
from a local DHCP server at startup.
.PP
DHCP is enabled automatically when
.B LOCALIP
is not set in the environment, /bootopts, or passed to ktcp.
To force DHCP even when a local IP is configured, use the
.B \-d
flag.
.SH CONFIGURATION
DHCP behavior is controlled by environment variables set in
.B /bootopts
or
.BR /etc/profile .
.PP
When
.B LOCALIP
is set, ktcp uses that address and DHCP is disabled.
When
.B LOCALIP
is not set, ktcp enables DHCP and negotiates an address.
.PP
The network configuration file
.B /etc/net.cfg
sets default values for
.BR localip ,
.BR gateway ,
and
.BR netmask .
These are passed to ktcp by the
.B net
script.
If
.B localip
is empty, DHCP will be used.
.SH STATE MACHINE
The client follows the standard DHCP exchange:
.PP
.RS
.nf
DISCOVER \(-> OFFER \(-> REQUEST \(-> ACK \(-> BOUND
.fi
.RE
.PP
1. Sends a broadcast DISCOVER on UDP port 67.
.br
2. Receives OFFER from a DHCP server.
.br
3. Sends a REQUEST for the offered address.
.br
4. Receives ACK and applies the lease (IP, netmask, gateway).
.PP
If a NAK is received at any stage, the client restarts from DISCOVER with a new
transaction ID.
.SH RETRY
Exponential backoff is used for retries:
.IP \(bu 2
Initial timeout: 4 ticks
.IP \(bu 2
Doubles each retry, capped at 16 ticks
.IP \(bu 2
After 5 failed retries, restarts from INIT
.PP
Once the address is bound, the retry timer is disabled.
.SH OPTIONS REQUESTED
The client requests the following DHCP options:
.IP \(bu 2
Subnet mask (option 1)
.IP \(bu 2
Router / default gateway (option 3)
.IP \(bu 2
DNS server (option 6)
.IP \(bu 2
Lease time (option 51)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /bootopts
Boot options file.
Set
.B LOCALIP=
to use a static address, or leave unset for DHCP.
.TP
.B /etc/net.cfg
Network configuration file sourced by
.BR /bin/net .
Contains default values for
.BR localip ,
.BR gateway ,
.BR netmask ,
and link type.
.TP
.B /bin/net
Network startup script that starts ktcp with the configured options.
.SH EXAMPLES
To use DHCP, leave
.B LOCALIP
unset in /bootopts and start networking:
.PP
.RS
.nf
net start ne0
.fi
.RE
.PP
To use a static address, set it in /bootopts:
.PP
.RS
.nf
LOCALIP=192.168.1.100
GATEWAY=192.168.1.1
NETMASK=255.255.255.0
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
Only one DHCP client can run per interface.
The client uses UDP port 68 and does not renew the lease before expiry.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR netconf (8),
.BR ifconfig (8),
.BR ktcp (8).
